{"job_title": "Commercial Analysis Senior Associate", "job_location": "West Jakarta, DKI Jakarta", "job_department": "Management and Consultancy", "job_url": "https://www.kalibrr.com/c/astro-technologies-indonesia/jobs/263761", "first_seen": "2026-04-25 15:51:46", "base_salary": "0", "job_type": "Full time", "job_level": "Bachelor", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-12-10 17:00:00", "last_seen": "2026-02-10 06:01:24", "is_active": "True", "company": "Astro Technologies Indonesia", "company_url": "https://www.kalibrr.com/id-ID/c/astro-technologies-indonesia/jobs", "job_board": "Kalibrr", "job_board_url": "https://www.kalibrr.com/id-ID/home", "job_age": "expired", "work_arrangement": "Hybrid", "desc": "Commercial Analysis Senior Associate Management and Consultancy About Astro  \n\n ASTRO is Indonesia's quick commerce company that delivers groceries and essentials to your door within 15 minutes. Founded in 2021 by a group of seasoned e-commerce executives and is backed trusted international investors, it is our mission to make people's lives simpler and easier by saving them time, energy, and money. \n\n Just like real Astronauts that take off into outer space, Astro embodies the values of being fast, bold, adventurous, and technologically advanced. \n\n Interested in working for a company that pushes the boundaries and strives to be the best? Join us now to be a part of this ground-breaking mission! \n\n  About this Position  \n\n This role drives commercial performance by translating data-driven insights into actionable strategies that support growth, profitability, and business OKRs. You will act as a key commercial driver, monitoring business performance, identifying risks and opportunities, and collaborating with cross-functional teams to ensure effective execution. The role combines hands-on analytics with strategic thinking to guide decisions at both SKU and business-unit levels. \n\n   Job Description   \n\n \n\t Formulate and execute impactful commercial strategies to drive growth, profitability, and attain business objectives. \n\t Take a proactive lead as the main business driver for commercial business unit, shaping the strategic direction and actively seeking growth opportunities. \n\t Monitor and take ownerships of OKRs, key business metrics, and profitability indicators, identify and take decisive actions when OKRs are at risk. \n\t Perform market analysis to identify trends, opportunities, and challenges on commercial operations. \n\t Collaborate with cross-functional stakeholders to drive continuous improvements in both on a regular and project basis. \n\t Prepare presentations for performance and management-related reviews, ensuring clear communication of insights and strategic initiatives. \n\t Support commercial teams in understanding data points, insights, and analysis, providing necessary training to enhance the team's understanding and application of data-driven strategies. Education: Bachelor’s degree in Business, Economics, Engineering, or other quantitative field. \n\t Experience: 2–4 years in business analysis, category support, or commercial operations within retail/FMCG/e-commerce/e-groceries/fresh and frozen food \n\t Analytics Skills: Solid Excel/Google Sheets. \n\t Retail Fluency: Comfortable with core metrics (margin %, velocity, OOS, Impression, CVR) and basic quality-control concepts for fresh &amp; frozen categories. \n\t Soft Skills: Structured thinker who enjoys working with numbers, works well in cross-functional teams, and adapts quickly in a fast paced environment. \n\t Mindset: Growth-oriented, hands-on, and proactive in spotting opportunities and driving small process tweaks to completion."}
{"job_title": "Adventurous English Teacher for Bandung!", "job_location": "Bandung, West Java (Jawa Barat)", "job_department": "Education and Training", "job_url": "https://www.kalibrr.com/c/ef-english-first-eduka-group/jobs/254043", "first_seen": "2026-04-25 15:51:46", "base_salary": "0", "job_type": "Full time", "job_level": "Bachelor", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-08-24 17:00:00", "last_seen": "2025-04-15 09:45:22", "is_active": "True", "company": "English 1 Eduka Group", "company_url": "https://www.kalibrr.com/id-ID/c/ef-english-first-eduka-group/jobs", "job_board": "Kalibrr", "job_board_url": "https://www.kalibrr.com/id-ID/home", "job_age": "expired", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Adventurous English Teacher for Bandung! Education and Training An English teacher at English 1 is responsible for teaching English to children and teenagers, and providing a high-quality learning experience: \n\n \n\t Teaching: Plan and deliver lessons to students aged 3–18 years old. Use electronic media and English 1-developed courseware to teach English. \n\t Student development: Monitor students' development and evaluate their progress. Provide guidance for improvement to students and their parents. \n\t Class records: Maintain student and class records. \n\t Marketing: Participate in marketing and off-site events. \n\t Placement tests: Conduct placement tests. \n\t Out-of-class exercises: Assign and evaluate out-of-class exercises. \n\t Social activities: Participate in social activities with students to encourage oral English proficiency. Start Your Teaching Adventure in Bandung!  \n\n Are you ready to take the next step in your teaching career and make a real impact in Indonesia? An exciting opportunity awaits in the beautiful Bandung area — where education, culture, and nature come together. \n\n  What You Need to Get Started  \n\n  Start Date : March 2026 \nBegin your journey with our comprehensive pre-service training before stepping into the classroom. \n\n  Location : Bandung Regency \nTeach in a dynamic environment just outside Bandung city, surrounded by stunning landscapes, rich culture, and welcoming communities. \n\n  Work Schedule : 6-day work week \nThis is a full-time position with a six-day teaching schedule. \n\n  Education Requirements  \nA Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in an English-related field is required. \n\n  Teaching Experience  \nAt least one year of relevant teaching experience is highly valued. A reference from a previous employer will strengthen your application. \n\n  Passion for Education  \nPrevious teaching experience is a plus — be ready to share what you’ve taught and what you enjoy most about the classroom. \n\n  What We’re Looking For  \nStrong self-motivation, flexibility, resilience, and attention to detail are essential for success in this role. \n\n  Training Program  \nYou will take part in an engaging three-week training program designed to build practical teaching skills and confidence. \n\n  Professional Standards  \nTeachers are expected to follow English 1’s Dress Code and Code of Conduct at all times. \n\n  Contract Commitment  \nA minimum one-year contract is required, offering stability and professional growth within a supportive team. \n\n  Required Documents  \nOnce hired, you will need to prepare an SKCK, NPWP, degree and transcript, and a CIMB Niaga Payroll bank account number. \n\n  Relocation Readiness  \nCandidates must be willing to relocate and make Bandung their new home. \n\n  Application Language  \nAll applications must be submitted in English. \n\n If you’re ready to inspire learners, grow professionally, and experience life in one of Indonesia’s most vibrant regions, this could be the perfect next chapter in your teaching journey."}
